              A federal judge calls the $1.92 million damage award against P2P user Jammie Thomas-Rasset "monstrous and shocking" and a "gross injustice." Today he cut the award from $80,000 per song to $2,250.<BR><BR><a href='http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/news/2010/01/judge-slashes-monstrous-jammie-thomas-p2p-award-by-35x.ars'>Read the whole story</a>

              

              
              
