          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              If I get caught stealing 2 CDs from Walmart, I sit in jail for a month or so, pay a small fine, and I owe Walmart 20-25 dollars. If I steal the exact same CDs over the internet, I suddenly owe $54,000, with no jail time or fine. WTF? Stealing music is stealing music, regardless of delivery method. She should only have to pay a fine, the retail value of the music, and sit in jail for a month or so, just like stealing the physical copies.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
